blocks.name: bnj110
blocks.content: Well-founded induction restricted to a set ( ` A e. _V ` ). The proof has been taken from Chapter 4 of Don Monk's notes on Set Theory. See ~ http://euclid.colorado.edu/~~monkd/setth.pdf . (Contributed by Jonathan Ben-Naim, 3-Jun-2011.) (New usage is discouraged.)

blocks.content: Well-founded induction restricted to a set ( ` A e. _V ` ). The proof has been taken from Chapter 4 of Don Monk's notes on Set Theory. See ~ http://euclid.colorado.edu/~~monkd/setth.pdf . (Contributed by Jonathan Ben-Naim, 3-Jun-2011.) (New usage is discouraged.)

thm bnj157(setvar s0, setvar s1, class c0, class c1, wff w0, wff w1) {
